    "comment": "Rationale: Knockdown of ARP2/3 results in a lower spine density.\n\n8/2/2018 Pim\n- Data looks at cocalization of PSD95 and SV2 spots as a readout for synapse formation. Authors show that ACTR3 is located at the postsynaptic side. ACTR3 is a known actin remodeling protein part of the Arp2/3 complex.. Experimental description: Cell Culture and Transfection-Hippocampal low density cultures were prepared as described previously (18). Reference 18 is entitled: Rat Hippocampal Neurons in Low-density Culture (Banker, G., and Goslin, K., eds) pp. 339-370, MIT Press, Cambridge, MA",
